Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Imagination and the Suburbs
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00d0sjj
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 25 Aug 2008
IMAGINATION AND THE SUBURB Why is the dream of suburbia so often portrayed as a nightmare? In part two of a series exploring how imagination and reality combine to create the environments in which we live, Laurie Taylor discusses facts and fantasies of suburban life with writer Iain Sinclair and sociologists Paul Barker and Dr Nick Hubble. Show less